<br>
1) Lower Guk. King Room.  Yes, the King room.  For some reason we have figured out how to own this bugger, and we have spaced out the remaining room pops so we could just pull from herbie, noble, water elemental etc.  Well, in a big downtime between spawns, our cleric tells the warrior to pull the live keep.<br>
&lt;cleric (Peeta)&gt; Hey Z. go pull the live tower<br>
&lt;war (zgog)&gt; ok.....how much?<br>
&lt;peeta&gt; All of it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Ry, load your ae's<br>
&lt;me&gt; k........<br>
&lt;zgog&gt; ok, got about 6 or 7 inc<br>
&lt;me&gt; ok, i am dumping a huge nuke on these buggers, be rdy to peel and heal <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
the tank brings actually about 5 mobs, most wan's and vis. long since green to me. I knew still that even if supernova landed, they would not be dead, and wanting to put some hurt on me.<br>
&lt;me&gt; Inc Supernova, be rdy for lag and a world of hurt<br>
The usual message comes up **target is hit for 854 damage**....only it does this message 5 times. that's some nice damage <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Immediately following my ae, our cleric drops his ae, and the shammy drops his ae, completely finishing off the mobs.  The tank just sat there and laughed.  We then proceeded to finish off the live keep. About 30 minutes later we get pull some more of the live keep, and a druid says in /ooc ummmmm, live tower camped.  I gave him a tell apologizing for our pulling, and he just laughed and said that he didn't mind but he got a little scared when he saw 8 mobs flying by him.<br>
<br>
The 2nd time I used Supernova, and the one I still believe is funnier, is in ToFS.  It was me, tank (zgog again), druid, and a bard.  We were on 2nd floor, and i was the only one w/ ITU, and it's self only. So, we decide we need to clear the floor before we head up to 3. We start single pulling.  So, I drop a draught and a stun, and notice that those 2 spells more than finishes them off, which begins this conversation<br>
&lt;me&gt; hey z, pull the whole floor<br>
&lt;tank (zgog)&gt; k......why?<br>
&lt;me&gt; cause i think supernova can kill them in one shot.<br>
&lt;zgog&gt; ok, here goes<br>
about 15 seconds later<br>
&lt;zgog&gt; inc....lots, don't cast till i tell you too<br>
&lt;me&gt; k<br>
once the mobs all finally get there....<br>
&lt;me&gt; inc supernova be rdy for big lag<br>
**target is hit for 854 dmg**<br>
that message scrolls by 12 times!!!!!!!!!<br>
The entire train of mobs just drops on the spot. then i sat down and figured out that that is approximately 11,500 dmg in one nuke!  the group just drops their collective jaws and the tank runs out and grabs the rest of the floor.<br>
<br>
I can honestly say I have rarely used this spell. More of a show off piece than anything else.  I cannot think of a true practical use for it, other than AE groups.  With the lvl of mobs we are hitting. if you use this and they aggro on you, be rdy to have your cleric rez you.  But I actually found out a fun, if not practical use for this spell.  Too bad it can't actually be of true use......<br>
Has anyone else had funny stories relating to this spell.....or any ideas on practical applications of this spell?<br>
